entries.name: owl2:AllDifferent
entries.description: The class of collections of pairwise different individuals.

entries.name: owl2:AllDisjointClasses
entries.description: The class of collections of pairwise disjoint classes.

entries.name: owl2:AllDisjointProperties
entries.description: The class of collections of pairwise disjoint properties.

entries.name: owl2:Annotation
entries.description: The class of annotated annotations for which the RDF serialization consists of an annotated subject, predicate and object.

entries.name: owl2:AnnotationProperty
entries.description: The class of annotation properties.

entries.name: owl2:AsymmetricProperty
entries.description: The class of asymmetric properties.

entries.name: owl2:Axiom
entries.description: The class of annotated axioms for which the RDF serialization consists of an annotated subject, predicate and object.

entries.name: owl2:Class
entries.description: The class of OWL classes.

entries.name: owl2:DataRange
entries.description: The class of OWL data ranges, which are special kinds of datatypes. Note: The use of the IRI owl:DataRange has been deprecated as of OWL 2. The IRI rdfs:Datatype SHOULD be used instead.

entries.name: owl2:DatatypeProperty
entries.description: The class of data properties.

entries.name: owl2:DeprecatedClass
entries.description: The class of deprecated classes.

entries.name: owl2:DeprecatedProperty
entries.description: The class of deprecated properties.

entries.name: owl2:FunctionalProperty
entries.description: The class of functional properties.

entries.name: owl2:InverseFunctionalProperty
entries.description: The class of inverse-functional properties.

entries.name: owl2:IrreflexiveProperty
entries.description: The class of irreflexive properties.

entries.name: owl2:NamedIndividual
entries.description: The class of named individuals.

entries.name: owl2:NegativePropertyAssertion
entries.description: The class of negative property assertions.

entries.name: owl2:Nothing
entries.description: This is the empty class.

entries.name: owl2:ObjectProperty
entries.description: The class of object properties.

entries.name: owl2:Ontology
entries.description: The class of ontologies.

entries.name: owl2:OntologyProperty
entries.description: The class of ontology properties.

entries.name: owl2:ReflexiveProperty
entries.description: The class of reflexive properties.

entries.name: owl2:Restriction
entries.description: The class of property restrictions.

entries.name: owl2:SymmetricProperty
entries.description: The class of symmetric properties.

entries.name: owl2:Thing
entries.description: The class of OWL individuals.

entries.name: owl2:TransitiveProperty
entries.description: The class of transitive properties.

entries.name: owl2:allValuesFrom
entries.description: The property that determines the class that a universal property restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:annotatedProperty
entries.description: The property that determines the predicate of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

entries.name: owl2:annotatedSource
entries.description: The property that determines the subject of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

entries.name: owl2:annotatedTarget
entries.description: The property that determines the object of an annotated axiom or annotated annotation.

entries.name: owl2:assertionProperty
entries.description: The property that determines the predicate of a negative property assertion.

entries.name: owl2:backwardCompatibleWith
entries.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is backward compatible with another ontology.

entries.name: owl2:bottomDataProperty
entries.description: The data property that does not relate any individual to any data value.

entries.name: owl2:bottomObjectProperty
entries.description: The object property that does not relate any two individuals.

entries.name: owl2:cardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:complementOf
entries.description: The property that determines that a given class is the complement of another class.

entries.name: owl2:datatypeComplementOf
entries.description: The property that determines that a given data range is the complement of another data range with respect to the data domain.

entries.name: owl2:deprecated
entries.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given entity has been deprecated.

entries.name: owl2:differentFrom
entries.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are different.

entries.name: owl2:disjointUnionOf
entries.description: The property that determines that a given class is equivalent to the disjoint union of a collection of other classes.

entries.name: owl2:disjointWith
entries.description: The property that determines that two given classes are disjoint.

entries.name: owl2:distinctMembers
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of pairwise different individuals in a owl:AllDifferent axiom.

entries.name: owl2:equivalentClass
entries.description: The property that determines that two given classes are equivalent, and that is used to specify datatype definitions.

entries.name: owl2:equivalentProperty
entries.description: The property that determines that two given properties are equivalent.

entries.name: owl2:hasKey
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of properties that jointly build a key.

entries.name: owl2:hasSelf
entries.description: The property that determines the property that a self restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:hasValue
entries.description: The property that determines the individual that a has-value restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:incompatibleWith
entries.description: The annotation property that indicates that a given ontology is incompatible with another ontology.

entries.name: owl2:intersectionOf
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build an intersection.

entries.name: owl2:inverseOf
entries.description: The property that determines that two given properties are inverse.

entries.name: owl2:maxCardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:maxQualifiedCardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a maximum qualified cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:members
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of members in either a owl:AllDifferent, owl:AllDisjointClasses or owl:AllDisjointProperties axiom.

entries.name: owl2:minCardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:minQualifiedCardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of a minimum qualified cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:onClass
entries.description: The property that determines the class that a qualified object cardinality restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:onDataRange
entries.description: The property that determines the data range that a qualified data cardinality restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:onDatatype
entries.description: The property that determines the datatype that a datatype restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:onProperties
entries.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that a property restriction on an n-ary data range refers to.

entries.name: owl2:onProperty
entries.description: The property that determines the property that a property restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:oneOf
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of individuals or data values that build an enumeration.

entries.name: owl2:priorVersion
entries.description: The annotation property that indicates the predecessor ontology of a given ontology.

entries.name: owl2:propertyChainAxiom
entries.description: The property that determines the n-tuple of properties that build a sub property chain of a given property.

entries.name: owl2:propertyDisjointWith
entries.description: The property that determines that two given properties are disjoint.

entries.name: owl2:qualifiedCardinality
entries.description: The property that determines the cardinality of an exact qualified cardinality restriction.

entries.name: owl2:sameAs
entries.description: The property that determines that two given individuals are equal.

entries.name: owl2:someValuesFrom
entries.description: The property that determines the class that an existential property restriction refers to.

entries.name: owl2:sourceIndividual
entries.description: The property that determines the subject of a negative property assertion.

entries.name: owl2:targetIndividual
entries.description: The property that determines the object of a negative object property assertion.

entries.name: owl2:targetValue
entries.description: The property that determines the value of a negative data property assertion.

entries.name: owl2:topDataProperty
entries.description: The data property that relates every individual to every data value.

entries.name: owl2:topObjectProperty
entries.description: The object property that relates every two individuals.

entries.name: owl2:unionOf
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of classes or data ranges that build a union.

entries.name: owl2:versionInfo
entries.description: The annotation property that provides version information for an ontology or another OWL construct.

entries.name: owl2:withRestrictions
entries.description: The property that determines the collection of facet-value pairs that define a datatype restriction.
